{
  "doc_id": "39523",
  "text": "Rachlin and Baron in [CITATION_1] argued whether the measurements of compressed sensing can prepare an approach to obtain perfect secrecy simultaneously or not. They investigate the achievability of perfect secrecy by using the measurement matrix of compressive sampling as a key for encrypting the transmitted signal and they proved compressed sensing-based encryption cannot achieve perfect secrecy.",
